                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Russell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Loomis informs Mr. Russell that in view of the fact that the Government of
                    Panama has been thoroughly established and has been recognized by the civilized
                    nations of the world it is not now regarded as competent to submit to a
                    plebiscite the question of its independence.</p>
                <p>The celebration of a treaty of friendship, commerce, and navigation between
                    Colombia and Panama will be pleasing to the President, as well as the settlement
                    by arbitration of all questions not disposed of in said treaty.)</p>
            </div>
